## âš™ï¸ Getting Started

### ğŸ§° Prerequisites

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/)
- [Supabase account](https://supabase.com/)

### ğŸš€ Installation

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/smart-complaint-management-system.git

# 2. Navigate to the project directory
cd smart-complaint-management-system

# 3. Install dependencies
npm install

# 4. Start the development server
npm run dev
````

---

## ğŸ” Supabase Setup

1. Create a Supabase project.
2. Enable **Email/Password Authentication**.
3. Create a `complaints` table with fields like:

   * `id`, `title`, `description`, `status`, `user_id`, `assigned_to`
4. Create `.env` and add your keys:

```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your-url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
```

